Q: I don't want to select existing post. I want to create Ad for that post to increase its comment, like, share.

Ans: If you don’t want to use the existing post, create a new ad in Meta Ads Manager with the same image/video and similar caption.

This ad can still get:

✔ Likes
✔ Comments
✔ Shares
✔ Reactions

Steps in Meta Ads Manager
1. Create Campaign

Go to Meta Ads Manager → Create

Choose objective: Engagement

2. Ad Set Level

Choose:

Conversion location: On your ad
Engagement type: Post Engagement
3. Audience

Target people likely to engage:

Example:

Country: Bangladesh or United States
Age: 18–40
Gender: All
Interests: related to your niche
4. Placements

Use:

Facebook Feed
Instagram Feed
Reels
Stories
5. Ad Level

Here create the ad manually:

Select your Facebook Page
Select your Instagram account (optional)

Then upload:

Image / Video
Primary text (caption)
Headline (optional)

Use engaging text like:

“🔥 What do you think about this?
Comment below 👇
Tag your friend ❤️”

This creates a dark post (ad-only post).

People can:

Like it
Comment on it
Share it

But it will not appear on your Page timeline unless you publish it separately.

Best Trick

Use a controversial question or emotional text to increase comments:

Example:
“Do you agree or not?”

This often increases engagement fast.

